    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="105"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d105">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the Ambassador in
                        the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJG1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d105fn1">Sent to the United States Naval
                        Attaché, London, via Navy channels. After receiving this telegram, <persName
                            corresp="#p_WJG1">Winant</persName> cabled <persName corresp="#p_HHL1"
                            >Hopkins</persName>: “Would you be good enough to explain my journey to
                        Ed <persName corresp="#p_SERJ1">Stettinius</persName>. Telegrams to the
                        Department will continue to carry my name. …” <persName corresp="#p_HHL1"
                            >Hopkins</persName> forwarded the message to <persName
                            corresp="#p_SERJ1">Stettinius</persName> on November 11, 1943 (123
                            <persName corresp="#p_WJG1">Winant, John G.</persName>/250).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-08">8 November
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>To Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_WJG1">Winant</persName> from the
                    President.</p>
                <p>Your message of 8 November. I think it would be fine.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
